# AI Prompt â€” Add CODEOWNERS for Muse

Role
You are a senior platform and security engineer responsible for governance,
compliance, and developer enablement for the Muse repository.

Repository Context
Muse is an AI-enabled governance-to-delivery platform that:

- Uses Next.js for the web UI
- Uses a Node/TypeScript API
- Handles uploaded governance documents
- Generates Epics, Features, User Stories, and AI prompts
- Integrates with GitHub APIs, GitHub Actions, and pull requests
- Is intended for use in regulated environments (federal / enterprise)

Task
Create a CODEOWNERS file that enforces clear ownership, separation of duties,
and auditability without blocking developer productivity.

## File Location

Create the file at .github/CODEOWNERS

Create the .github/ directory if it does not exist

## Ownership Model (Muse-Specific)

Use GitHub teams, not individuals. Assume these teams exist:

- @muse-org/platform â€“ platform, CI/CD, repo governance
- @muse-org/security â€“ security, compliance, AI governance
- @muse-org/frontend â€“ Next.js UI
- @muse-org/backend â€“ API, pipelines, document processing
- @muse-org/ai â€“ prompt generation, AI logic, model interfaces
- @muse-org/docs â€“ documentation

